ered here.  (AHJ 0708)</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>SurroundingArea</Type><Text>The Southern Sun waterfront is perfectly positioned immediately outside the entrance to the popular Victoria and Alfred Waterfront. Ideally located for tourists wanting to be close to the city centre, and also for business clients, as the hotel sits opposite the city convention centre. The hotel has its own shuttle service to the V&amp;A [meaning unclear] Waterfront.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>RoomTypes</Type><Text>All the rooms are modern in décor, with light wood furnishings and light colours. All are medium in size and in good condition, with all the services expected from a first-class hotel. The bathrooms are also in good condition, and have a separate bath and shower.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>PropertyInformation</Type><Text>An attractive, purpose-built building painted white.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>DiningFacilities</Type><Text>Breakfast is served on the ground floor, and guests can either eat inside or outside. There is also a top-class restaurant offering an à la carte menu and a wide selection of South African wines. There is also a small cellar with a collection of wines and a cigar lounge.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>Short</Type><Text>The hotel has a large lobby with marble flooring and a high ceiling with retro lights hanging down. The reception is slick looking with a huge fish tank to its right and the hotel bar is at the back of the lobby, overlooking the hotel swimming pool.</Text></Description><Amenity><Text>Outdoor swimming pool</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Text>Air conditioning</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Text>Hair dryer</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Text>Car parking</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Text>Fitness room / Gym</Text></Amenity><Rating><System>Stars</System><Score>40</Score><Description>Four star</De